        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 2:44PM CDT by NWS Topeka KS</headline>
        <description>At 244 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Lone Elm, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Kincaid and Lone Elm.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
